<span id="freeTextContainer3833220303865607328">Ruth Sutton writes to the man she hates more than anyone else on the planet: the man she believes killed her daughter Lizzie four years earlier.<br/><br/>Oh Wow. I think I have went through the emotions reading this book. Love: for Ruth, having having to bring up her granddaughter on her own and try to put their life&apos;s back together. Hate: for the man who took Lizzie&apos;s life. This is a wonderfully written book about a woman who is trying to move on after the violent death of her daughter. I do recommend th</span>
  <span id="freeText3833220303865607328" style="display:none">Ruth Sutton writes to the man she hates more than anyone else on the planet: the man she believes killed her daughter Lizzie four years earlier.<br /><br />Oh Wow. I think I have went through the emotions reading this book. Love: for Ruth, having having to bring up her granddaughter on her own and try to put their life's back together. Hate: for the man who took Lizzie's life. This is a wonderfully written book about a woman who is trying to move on after the violent death of her daughter. I do recommend this book.</span>
