<div id="review_2166491835" class="review nosyndicate" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/2166491835" />
    <a title="Kayleigh" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/41516530-kayleigh"><img alt="Kayleigh" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1511222954p2/41516530.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/2166491835?book_show_action=true">Oct 28, 2017</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="Kayleigh" class="user" itemprop="url" name="Kayleigh" href="/user/show/41516530-kayleigh">Kayleigh</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer2166491835" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer1884747594534535419">This journey of a mother&apos;s shock, grief, fury and pain, told chronologically through letters to her daughter&apos;s murderer, packs quite the emotional punch. No parent should have to endure what Ruth went through and this was not the easiest of books to read in some places because of the subject matter. This is full of grit, palpable rage and a sorrow that tugs at the parts of the reader that can understand the ache for revenge, justice or just alleviation of the burden of grief. This book was a jou</span>
  <span id="freeText1884747594534535419" style="display:none">This journey of a mother's shock, grief, fury and pain, told chronologically through letters to her daughter's murderer, packs quite the emotional punch. No parent should have to endure what Ruth went through and this was not the easiest of books to read in some places because of the subject matter. This is full of grit, palpable rage and a sorrow that tugs at the parts of the reader that can understand the ache for revenge, justice or just alleviation of the burden of grief. This book was a journey through hatred and heartbreak. <br />I had a lot of respect for the ending; the realism of the conclusion of Ruth's letters was effective and honest. It probably won't linger with me for long, this didn't change my life or leave me unable to think about anything else, it was what it was. Cath Staincliffe wrote this brilliantly but I wasn't exactly hooked. Regardless, Ruth's voice was strong and realistic and enabled the reader to explore a plethora of very raw emotions and reactions to a parent's worst nightmare. </span>
  <a data-text-id="1884747594534535419" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


