<span id="freeTextContainer6973690293421453482">I can&apos;t remember the last time I stayed up to finish a book but this absolutely gripped me. Ruth thought she and her daughter were close, but when Lizzie is brutally murdered, she discovers how little she knows.<br/><br/>We&apos;re shown the unique perspective of the aftermath of a terrible crime, as Ruth struggles to accept the violent loss of her daughter, dealing with her own anger and hatred whilst helping to care for her young granddaughter. The events and evidence are steadily revealed as the police inve</span>
  <span id="freeText6973690293421453482" style="display:none">I can't remember the last time I stayed up to finish a book but this absolutely gripped me. Ruth thought she and her daughter were close, but when Lizzie is brutally murdered, she discovers how little she knows.<br /><br />We're shown the unique perspective of the aftermath of a terrible crime, as Ruth struggles to accept the violent loss of her daughter, dealing with her own anger and hatred whilst helping to care for her young granddaughter. The events and evidence are steadily revealed as the police investigation progresses.<br /><br />I read Staincliffe's Looking For Trouble years ago and remembered the author when I came across this at the library. I will certainly seek out more of her work.</span>
